verses.roman:
tabe rājā aṭṭālikā haite talete āilā
kāśī-miśra, paḍichā-pātra, duṅhe ānāilā

synonyms: tabe—thereafter; rājā—the King; aṭṭālikā haite—from the top of the palace; talete—to the ground; āilā—came down; kāśī-miśra—of the name Kāśī Miśra; paḍichā-pātra—the inspector of the temple; duṅhe—both of them; ānāilā—called for.
translation: After this, King Pratāparudra came down from the top of his palace to the ground and called for Kāśī Miśra and the inspector of the temple.
